          <li>
            <a data-toggle="collapse" class="collapsed" href="#faq1">What is emotional fitness? <i
                class="ion-android-remove"></i></a>
            <div id="faq1" class="collapse" data-parent="#faq-list">
              <p>
                Emotional fitness commonly means the ability to emotionally adapt to any situation. We tend to think of
                it from a much broader perspective. Emotional fitness to us isn’t a dynamic measure, that defines you
                and typically holds steady, but is static, reflective of your current emotional state.
              </p>
            </div>
          </li>

          <li>
            <a data-toggle="collapse" href="#faq2" class="collapsed">How can you measure emotions? <i
                class="ion-android-remove"></i></a>
            <div id="faq2" class="collapse" data-parent="#faq-list">
              <p>
                Emotions seem borderline-incomprehensible, but the extent of emotions are not. There is a huge
                difference between content and ecstatic regardless of the fact that they both fall under the umbrella of
                "happy". This is what we measure - The degree to which you are feeling an emotion.
              </p>
            </div>
          </li>

          <li>
